Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Address - 	1055 Captain Cook Highway, Smithfield through to 6 Lesley Street

Land Area- 1324m² - 2 street access 

RPD-	Lot 1 on RP 738253  CTR 21207203

Frontage to Highway-26m x 50m depth Approx.

Zone-Commercial users

Current Improvements- 
   The highway side of the property has been the home of a vet for approx. 40 years and contains a 6 room consultation clinic with an undercover entry having to total floor area of approx.115m².
   The Lesley Street side contains a 2-bedroom residence of approx. 72m² including a carport. The balance of the site is turfed, gardens and car parking for 6-8 vehicles.

Development MCU- Plans have been lodged with council for an MCU approval for a 2 Level office building of 1000m² total over 2 levels with 23 on street carparks. The design is generic and can be adapted to suit an alternate use if required.


Highest & Best Use -	
   The site will lend itself to a wide and varied number of uses and enjoys maximumexposure to approx. 30,000 passing vehicles per day. 
Possible uses include 	
- Offices
- Retail (with Council approval)
- Fast Food Drive through
- Fuel
- Lifestyle/entertainment
- Medical, Professional, vet etc.
- Nursery
- Showroom

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: “THE ORANGE VET SITE” – OWNER RETIRING AFTER 40 YEARS OF PRACTICE
